   =20
      Active passive management
   =20
 =20

Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Ye Xie and Liz McCormick have sort of   a funny profile=
 of Josh Barrickman, who runs Vanguard Group Inc.=E2=80=99s Americas bond i=
ndexing business. You might think that the guy running $1 trillion of bond =
index funds would not have to make a lot of decisions =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=
=9Cjust buy the index=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0but in fact the way you run a=
 bond index fund is=C2=A0not=C2=A0by buying all the bonds in the index: The=
re are too many, and many of them don=E2=80=99t trade that much. Instead yo=
u buy a=C2=A0lot=C2=A0of the bonds in the index, try to get a representativ=
e sample, try to track the index, and end up making a lot of decisions. You=
 are in some sense much=C2=A0less=C2=A0active than an active bond manager, =
but on the other hand you run $1 trillion and they don=E2=80=99t:

That makes Barrickman exhibit A of a passive management revolution that=E2=
=80=99s reshaping the world of fixed-income, just as it did equities a deca=
de ago. No longer dominated by traders making multimillion-dollar bets and =
eating what they kill, the real money is flowing to guys like him, whose de=
cisions are increasingly rippling through markets.
=E2=80=9CWe do have size and scale, and that matters in the marketplace,=E2=
=80=9D Barrickman said in an interview. =E2=80=9CTracking is job one, two a=
nd three,=E2=80=9D he said, adding =E2=80=9Cif we can have a basis point a =
year, that=E2=80=99s a lot of real money.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6
Barrickman himself now oversees three of the world=E2=80=99s four largest b=
ond funds, including the $298 billion Vanguard Total Bond Market Index Fund=
, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.
That means many of the decisions he makes, like which bonds to buy when try=
ing to replicate his funds=E2=80=99 underlying benchmarks, can have big con=
sequences for the market (the Vanguard Total International Bond Index Fund,=
 for example, only holds roughly half the 13,000 bonds in the index it trac=
ks.)
=E2=80=9CWe have to be, by definition, overweight some places and underweig=
ht others to build a sample,=E2=80=9D Barrickman said. =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99=
re dealing in a market that forces us to take some active positions.=E2=80=
=9D

If you run $1 trillion of indexed bond money and capture one basis point a =
year with your active decisionmaking, that=E2=80=99s $100 million of alpha.=
=C2=A0

