blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; =
background-color: #ccc;">  a funny profile of Josh Barrickman</a>, who runs=
 Vanguard Group Inc.=E2=80=99s Americas bond indexing business. You might t=
hink that the guy running $1 trillion of bond index funds would not have to=
 make a lot of decisions =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cjust buy the index=E2=80=
=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0but in fact the way you run a bond index fund is=C2=A0<e=
m>not=C2=A0</em>by buying all the bonds in the index: There are too many, a=
nd many of them don=E2=80=99t trade that much. Instead you buy a=C2=A0<em>l=
ot=C2=A0</em>of the bonds in the index, try to get a representative sample,=
 try to track the index, and end up making a lot of decisions. You are in s=
ome sense much=C2=A0<em>less=C2=A0</em>active than an active bond manager, =
but on the other hand you run $1 trillion and they don=E2=80=99t:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That makes Barrickman exhibit A of a passive m=
anagement revolution that=E2=80=99s reshaping the world of fixed-income, ju=
st as it did equities a decade ago. No longer dominated by traders making m=
ultimillion-dollar bets and eating what they kill, the real money is flowin=
g to guys like him, whose decisions are increasingly rippling through marke=
ts.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWe do have size and scale, and that m=
atters in the marketplace,=E2=80=9D Barrickman said in an interview. =E2=80=
=9CTracking is job one, two and three,=E2=80=9D he said, adding =E2=80=9Cif=
 we can have a basis point a year, that=E2=80=99s a lot of real money.=E2=
=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Barrickman himself now oversees three of the w=
orld=E2=80=99s four largest bond funds, including the $298 billion Vanguard=
 Total Bond Market Index Fund, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That means many of the decisions he makes, lik=
e which bonds to buy when trying to replicate his funds=E2=80=99 underlying=
 benchmarks, can have big consequences for the market (the Vanguard Total I=
nternational Bond Index Fund, for example, only holds roughly half the 13,0=
00 bonds in the index it tracks.)</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWe have to be, by definition, overwei=
ght some places and underweight others to build a sample,=E2=80=9D Barrickm=
an said. =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re dealing in a market that forces us to take =
some active positions.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you run $1 trillion of indexed bond money a=
nd capture one basis point a year with your active decisionmaking, that=E2=
=80=99s $100 million of alpha.=C2=A0</p>
